<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES FS-5106 AND FS-6206 - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300809">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300809" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300809" filename="../figg13/G1300809.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Input Shaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six bolts, jar the front bearing cover with a rubber mallet and remove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300810">Figure 10</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the oil seal from the cover (inset).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300810" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300810" filename="../figg13/G1300810.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Jar Front Bearing Cover With Mallet</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft assembly from the transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300811">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300811" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300811" filename="../figg13/G1300811.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Remove Input Shaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a chisel to remove bearing cage and rollers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300812">Figure 12</hotlnk>). Install bearing puller and remove bearing race from the
                input shaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300812" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300812" filename="../figg13/G1300812.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Remove Bearing Cage and Rollers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
